<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 5:17AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>Patchy fog has developed across portions of southern Connecticut
early this morning. Visibilities may be reduced to a half mile or
less at times. With temperatures near freezing, a few icy spots
may develop on roads and sidewalks.
Motorists should exercise caution by reducing speed, leaving
extra space between vehicles, and using low-beam headlights in
areas of low visibility.</description>
